column37: To be considered `complete`, a sequences MUST 1) include the first V segment codon that encodes the mature polypeptide chain (i.e. after the leader sequence); 2) include the last complete codon of the J segment (i.e. 1 bp 5' of the J->C splice site); 3) provide sequence information for all positions between 1) and 2). To be considered `complete & untemplated`, the sections of the sequences defined in points 1) to 3) of the previous sentence MUST be untemplated, i.e. MUST NOT overlap with the primers used in library preparation.
